{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GbezH4EWjVcuTmGF449ACb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 9-5: Multi-stack docs and remaining consumers\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer initializing a multi-stack project,\n     8→I want AGENTS.md and README to reflect all detected stacks,\n     9→So that AI agents and humans know how to build/test all components.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given a multi-stack project, when `generateAgentsMdContent()` is called, then it lists build/test commands for all detected stacks <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `['nodejs', 'rust']`, when `getStackLabel()` is called, then it returns `'Node.js (package.json) + Rust (Cargo.toml)'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given a multi-stack project, when `getProjectName()` is called, then it tries each stack's project file (package.json name, Cargo.toml [package] name) and returns the first found <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC4: Given state has `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']`, when `verify/env.ts` checks for nodejs, then it uses `stacks.includes('nodejs')` instead of `stack === 'nodejs'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC5: Given all changes complete, when `npm test` runs, then all existing single-stack tests pass with 0 regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→\n    19→## Technical Notes\n    20→\n    21→### Changes to `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts`\n    22→\n    23→**`getStackLabel()` (L50):**\n    24→Currently accepts `string | null`. Add overload for `string[]`:\n    25→- If `string[]`, map each to its label (`nodejs` → `Node.js (package.json)`, `rust` → `Rust (Cargo.toml)`, `python` → `Python (requirements.txt)`) and join with ` + `.\n    26→- If `string`, keep existing behavior (backward compat).\n    27→\n    28→**`generateAgentsMdContent()` (L63):**\n    29→Currently accepts a single stack. Add overload for `StackDetection[]`:\n    30→- If `StackDetection[]`, generate a section for each stack with its build/test commands:\n    31→  ```markdown\n    32→  ## Build & Test\n    33→\n    34→  ### Node.js (frontend/)\n    35→  - `cd frontend && npm ci`\n    36→  - `cd frontend && npm test`\n    37→\n    38→  ### Rust (backend/)\n    39→  - `cd backend && cargo build`\n    40→  - `cd backend && cargo test`\n    41→  ```\n    42→- If single stack, keep existing output unchanged.\n    43→\n    44→**`getCoverageTool()` (if present):**\n    45→Accept `string | string[]`. If array, return primary stack's (`[0]`) coverage tool.\n    46→\n    47→**`getProjectName()`:**\n    48→Try each stack's project file in order:\n    49→1. `package.json` → `name` field\n    50→2. `Cargo.toml` → `[package]` → `name` field\n    51→3. `pyproject.toml` → `[project]` → `name` field\n    52→Return the first found, fall back to directory name.\n    53→\n    54→### Changes to `src/modules/verify/env.ts`\n    55→\n    56→Find all occurrences of `state.stack === 'nodejs'` (and similar for other stacks) and replace with `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs')`. The `?.` handles old state objects that might not have `stacks` yet.\n    57→\n    58→This file has 1-2 stack reference points — minor change.\n    59→\n    60→### Changes to `src/commands/teardown.ts`\n    61→\n    62→Reads `stack` from state for stack-specific cleanup. Update to read `stacks` from state, use `stacks[0]` (primary) for any stack-specific teardown logic. Minor change — 1-2 references.\n    63→\n    64→### Changes to `src/templates/readme.ts`\n    65→\n    66→**`getInstallCommand()` (L72):**\n    67→Accept `string | string[]`. If array, render per-stack install commands:\n    68→```markdown\n    69→### Node.js\n    70→npm ci\n    71→\n    72→### Rust\n    73→cargo build\n    74→```\n    75→If single string, keep existing output.\n    76→\n    77→### Import changes\n    78→\n    79→Add `StackDetection` import from `../../lib/stack-detect` in docs-scaffold.ts and dockerfile-template.ts.\n    80→\n    81→### Test files\n    82→\n    83→Update `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts`:\n    84→- `getStackLabel(['nodejs', 'rust'])` → `'Node.js (package.json) + Rust (Cargo.toml)'`\n    85→- `getStackLabel('nodejs')` → existing output (backward compat)\n    86→- `generateAgentsMdContent()` with multi-stack → sections for each stack\n    87→- `getProjectName()` with multi-stack → finds first available name\n    88→\n    89→Update tests for `verify/env.ts` and `teardown.ts` if they have stack-related test cases — update assertions to use `stacks` array.\n    90→\n    91→## Files to Change\n    92→\n    93→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Update `getStackLabel()` (L50) to accept `string[]`, update `generateAgentsMdContent()` (L63) to accept `StackDetection[]` with per-stack sections, update `getProjectName()` to try multiple stack project files\n    94→- `src/modules/verify/env.ts` — Replace `state.stack === 'nodejs'` with `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs')` (and similar for other stacks)\n    95→- `src/commands/teardown.ts` — Update stack references to use `stacks[0]` from state\n    96→- `src/templates/readme.ts` — Update `getInstallCommand()` (L72) to accept `string[]` and render per-stack commands\n    97→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — Add multi-stack label, multi-stack AGENTS.md, and getProjectName tests\n    98→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ki63cWXHdDviaA8PEm2Nkw","session_id":"58ae4f51-bff6-4a66-807a-d4f10c8bdaa3","uuid":"89fcf021-62e6-4ec9-b1b3-674c97fa0678","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:39:48.828Z"}
