 function. It is under the 300-line limit but very close. A future story should consider extracting the multi-stack generation into a separate module.\n- The story test spec (6.2) asked to verify `cd frontend && npm ci` but the actual AGENTS.md template uses `npm install` (not `npm ci`). The test verifies `cd frontend && npm install` which matches the actual generated content. The AC text mentions `npm ci` but the existing single-stack template already uses `npm install`, so this is consistent.\n- The `verify-env.test.ts` required updating ~15 existing test locations to add `mockDetectStacks` calls alongside existing `mockDetectStack` calls, because `detectProjectType` (called internally by `buildVerifyImage`) now uses `detectStacks` instead of `detectStack`. This is a ripple effect of the detection method change but all tests remain green.\n- AC7 specifies `state.stacks?.[0]` for primary stack logic, but the actual implementation uses `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs')` which is more correct — it checks if nodejs is anywhere in the stacks array rather than only at index 0. This matches the story's own Task 5.1 specification."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa37ebf61cc0c04e4 (use SendMessage with to: 'aa37ebf61cc0c04e4' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 100211\ntool_uses: 80\nduration_ms: 500130</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58ae4f51-bff6-4a66-807a-d4f10c8bdaa3","uuid":"f6ee7524-d075-45f5-8d6c-8c40dbb1d378","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:50:22.428Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems 