updated\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/teardown.test.ts` — 1 new multi-stack teardown test\n\n**Results:** 3149 tests pass, 0 regressions. Story status set to `review`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- `docs-scaffold.ts` grew from 229 to ~295 lines with the `generateMultiStackAgentsMd` helper function. It is under the 300-line limit but very close. A future story should consider extracting the multi-stack generation into a separate module.\n- The story test spec (6.2) asked to verify `cd frontend && npm ci` but the actual AGENTS.md template uses `npm install` (not `npm ci`). The test verifies `cd frontend && npm install` which matches the actual generated content. The AC text mentions `npm ci` but the existing single-stack template already uses `npm install`, so this is consistent.\n- The `verify-env.test.ts` required updating ~15 existing test locations to add `mockDetectStacks` calls alongside existing `mockDetectStack` calls, because `detectProjectType` (called internally by `buildVerifyImage`) now uses `detectStacks` instead of `detectStack`. This is a ripple effect of the detection method change but all tests remain green.\n- AC7 specifies `state.stacks?.[0]` for primary stack logic, but the actual implementation uses `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs')` which is more correct — it checks if nodejs is anywhere in the stacks array rather than only at index 0. This matches the story's own Task 5.1 specification."}],"totalDurationMs":500130,"totalTokens":100211,"totalToolUseCount":80,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5040,"cache_read_input_tokens":94283,"output_tokens":887,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5040},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
