{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01A9q8RnkWAMwzdNuEy2GJf2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 9.5: Multi-stack docs and remaining consumers\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a developer initializing a multi-stack project,\n    10→I want AGENTS.md and README to reflect all detected stacks,\n    11→So that AI agents and humans know how to build/test all components.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→- [x] AC1: Given a multi-stack project with `StackDetection[]` containing nodejs (frontend/) and rust (backend/), when `generateAgentsMdContent()` is called with the detections, then it lists per-stack build/test command sections (e.g., `### Node.js (frontend/)` with `cd frontend && npm ci` and `### Rust (backend/)` with `cd backend && cargo build`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC2: Given `['nodejs', 'rust']`, when `getStackLabel()` is called, then it returns `'Node.js (package.json) + Rust (Cargo.toml)'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [x] AC3: Given a multi-stack project with both `package.json` and `Cargo.toml`, when `getProjectName()` is called, then it tries `package.json` name first, falls back to `Cargo.toml` [package] name, and returns the first found <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [x] AC4: Given `verify/env.ts` calls `detectProjectType()`, when the project contains multiple stacks, then `detectProjectType()` uses `detectStacks()` (plural) to detect the primary stack instead of `detectStack()` (singular), preserving the same return type <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→- [x] AC5: Given a multi-stack project, when `scaffoldDocs()` is called, then it passes `StackDetection[]` (not just primary stack) to `generateAgentsMdContent()` so the generated AGENTS.md covers all stacks <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→- [x] AC6: Given a multi-stack project with stacks `['nodejs', 'rust']`, when `readmeTemplate()` is called, then the README install section includes commands for all detected stacks (e.g., `npm install` and `cargo build`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→- [x] AC7: Given `teardown.ts` reads `state.stack` for stack-specific cleanup, when state has `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']`, then teardown uses `state.stacks?.[0]` (primary) for stack-specific logic like OTLP removal <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→- [x] AC8: Given all changes complete, when `npm test` runs, then all existing single-stack tests pass with 0 regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→\n    24→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    25→\n    26→- [x] Task 1: Update `generateAgentsMdContent()` to accept `StackDetection[]` (AC: #1, #5)\n    27→  - [x] 1.1 Add overload: if second parameter is `StackDetection[]`, generate per-stack sections with directory-relative commands (e.g., `cd frontend && npm ci`); if string/null, keep existing single-stack output unchanged\n    28→  - [x] 1.2 Import `StackDetection` type from `../../lib/stack-detect.js`\n    29→  - [x] 1.3 For root stacks (`dir === '.'`), omit the `cd` prefix — use bare commands (e.g., `npm install`)\n    30→  - [x] 1.4 For subdir stacks (`dir !== '.'`), prefix commands with `cd {dir} &&`\n    31→  - [x] 1.5 Use `getStackLabel(detection.stack)` for section headings, append `({dir})` when dir !== '.'\n    32→- [x] Task 2: Update `scaffoldDocs()` and `ScaffoldDocsOptions` to pass `StackDetection[]` (AC: #5)\n    33→  - [x] 2.1 Add `stacks?: StackDetection[]` to `ScaffoldDocsOptions` interface (keep `stack` for backward compat)\n    34→  - [x] 2.2 In `scaffoldDocs()`, if `opts.stacks` is provided and length > 1, call `generateAgentsMdContent(projectDir, stacks)` instead of `generateAgentsMdContent(projectDir, stack)`\n    35→  - [x] 2.3 Update caller in `init-project.ts` (~L143) to pass `allStacks` via the `stacks` option\n    36→- [x] Task 3: Update `readmeTemplate()` for multi-stack install commands (AC: #6)\n    37→  - [x] 3.1 Change `ReadmeTemplateConfig.stack` to `stack: string | string[] | null`\n    38→  - [x] 3.2 Update `getInstallCommand()` to accept `string | string[] | null`; if array, render per-stack install lines\n    39→  - [x] 3.3 Update caller in `scaffoldDocs()` (~L201) to pass `result.stacks` or `[stack]` to readme template\n    40→- [x] Task 4: Update `detectProjectType()` in `verify/env.ts` (AC: #4)\n    41→  - [x] 4.1 Import `detectStacks` instead of `detectStack` from `../../lib/stack-detect.js`\n    42→  - [x] 4.2 Call `detectStacks(projectDir)` and derive primary stack from root detection (same pattern as `init-project.ts` L69-71)\n    43→  - [x] 4.3 Keep return type unchanged (`ProjectType`) — this is about detection method, not return value\n    44→- [x] Task 5: Update `teardown.ts` stack references (AC: #7)\n    45→  - [x] 5.1 At L190, replace `state.stack === 'nodejs'` with `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs') ?? state.stack === 'nodejs'` (backward compat with old state files)\n    46→- [x] Task 6: Add tests for multi-stack AGENTS.md generation (AC: #1)\n    47→  - [x] 6.1 Test: `generateAgentsMdContent(dir, [{stack:'nodejs', dir:'frontend'}, {stack:'rust', dir:'backend'}])` → output contains `### Node.js (frontend/)` and `### Rust (backend/)`\n    48→  - [x] 6.2 Test: multi-stack AGENTS.md contains `cd frontend && npm ci` and `cd backend && cargo build`\n    49→  - [x] 6.3 Test: root stack (`dir: '.'`) has bare commands without `cd` prefix\n    50→  - [x] 6.4 Test: single-stack string argument still produces existing output (backward compat)\n    51→- [x] Task 7: Add tests for multi-stack README template (AC: #6)\n    52→  - [x] 7.1 Test: `getInstallCommand(['nodejs', 'rust'])` → includes both `npm install` and `cargo build`\n    53→  - [x] 7.2 Test: `getInstallCommand('python')` → existing output unchanged\n    54→- [x] Task 8: Add tests for `detectProjectType()` and teardown (AC: #4, #7)\n    55→  - [x] 8.1 Test: `detectProjectType()` with multi-stack project returns primary stack's project type\n    56→  - [x] 8.2 Test: teardown with `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']` in state triggers OTLP cleanup\n    57→- [x] Task 9: Run full test suite — verify zero regressions (AC: #8)\n    58→  - [x] 9.1 `npm test` passes all existing tests\n    59→  - [x] 9.2 Coverage remains above 90% target\n    60→\n    61→## Dev Notes\n    62→\n    63→### Architecture & Key Patterns\n    64→\n    65→- **Result\\<T\\> pattern:** All public functions return `Result<T>` using `ok()` / `fail()` from `../../types/result.js`. Do not throw.\n    66→- **File limit:** <300 lines per file. `docs-scaffold.ts` is currently 229 lines. Multi-stack AGENTS.md generation will add ~30-40 lines — should stay under 300. If it approaches the limit, extract a helper.\n    67→- **Module boundary:** `docs-scaffold.ts` exports via `src/modules/infra/index.ts`. Any new exports must be added there.\n    68→- **Backward compat:** All functions must accept their existing signature AND the new multi-stack signature. Use runtime `Array.isArray()` checks (same pattern as `dockerfile-template.ts` story 9-4).\n    69→\n    70→### Current Code (as of story 9-4)\n    71→\n    72→**`src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts`** — 229 lines. Contains:\n    73→- `getProjectName(projectDir)` — tries `package.json` → `Cargo.toml` → `basename`. Already handles multi-stack discovery order. **AC3 is already satisfied** by current implementation — verify with tests.\n    74→- `getStackLabel(stack: string | string[] | null)` — already handles `string[]` via recursive map+join. **AC2 is already satisfied** — the test at line 128 confirms it.\n    75→- `getCoverageTool(stack)` — returns coverage tool by stack name.\n    76→- `generateAgentsMdContent(projectDir, stack: string | null)` — single-stack only. **Needs multi-stack overload** for AC1.\n    77→- `scaffoldDocs(opts)` — orchestrates AGENTS.md, docs/, README creation. Calls `generateAgentsMdContent(projectDir, stack)` at L167. **Needs update** to pass `StackDetection[]` when available.\n    78→\n    79→**`src/modules/verify/env.ts`** — 300 lines. Contains:\n    80→- `detectProjectType(projectDir)` — calls `detectStack(projectDir)` (singular compat wrapper). **Needs update** to use `detectStacks()` for multi-stack awareness (AC4). The function at L69-79 uses `stack === 'nodejs'` pattern.\n    81→\n    82→**`src/commands/teardown.ts`** — Contains `state.stack === 'nodejs'` at L190 for OTLP cleanup. **Needs update** to check `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs')` (AC7).\n    83→\n    84→**`src/templates/readme.ts`** — 78 lines. Contains:\n    85→- `readmeTemplate(config)` — generates README.md content\n    86→- `getInstallCommand(stack: string | null)` — returns install command. **Needs multi-stack support** (AC6).\n    87→\n    88→**`src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`** — Calls `scaffoldDocs({ projectDir, stack, isJson })` at L143. Has `allStacks` available at L69. **Needs update** to pass `allStacks` through to scaffoldDocs.\n    89→\n    90→### Design Decisions\n    91→\n    92→1. **`getStackLabel` and `getProjectName` — already done.** Both already support multi-stack. `getStackLabel` accepts `string | string[] | null`. `getProjectName` tries `package.json` → `Cargo.toml` in order. No changes needed for AC2/AC3 — just verify with tests.\n    93→2. **`generateAgentsMdContent` overload:** Accept `(projectDir: string, stack: string | StackDetection[] | null)`. If `StackDetection[]`, generate per-stack sections. If string/null, existing behavior.\n    94→3. **`scaffoldDocs` interface extension:** Add optional `stacks?: StackDetection[]` to `ScaffoldDocsOptions`. When present and length > 1, pass to `generateAgentsMdContent`. Keeps backward compat — callers that don't pass `stacks` get existing behavior.\n    95→4. **`detectProjectType` update:** Replace `detectStack()` with `detectStacks()`, derive primary from root detection. Return type unchanged — still `ProjectType`. This is the minimal change for multi-stack awareness.\n    96→5. **`teardown.ts` — defensive fallback:** Use `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs') ?? state.stack === 'nodejs'` to handle both old and new state formats.\n    97→\n    98→### Important: Some ACs are already satisfied\n    99→\n   100→- **AC2** (`getStackLabel` with array): Already implemented and tested (docs-scaffold.ts L50-54, test L128-138).\n   101→- **AC3** (`getProjectName` with multi-stack): Already implemented — tries `package.json` → `Cargo.toml` → basename (docs-scaffold.ts L17-48, test L42-108).\n   102→- Verify these with existing tests. Do NOT re-implement.\n   103→\n   104→### `generateAgentsMdContent` multi-stack structure\n   105→\n   106→```markdown\n   107→# {projectName}\n   108→\n   109→## Stack\n   110→\n   111→- **Language/Runtime:** Node.js + Rust\n   112→\n   113→## Build & Test Commands\n   114→\n   115→### Node.js (frontend/)\n   116→```bash\n   117→cd frontend && npm install    # Install dependencies\n   118→cd frontend && npm run build  # Build the project\n   119→cd frontend && npm test       # Run tests\n   120→```\n   121→\n   122→### Rust (backend/)\n   123→```bash\n   124→cd backend && cargo build    # Build the project\n   125→cd backend && cargo test     # Run tests\n   126→cd backend && cargo tarpaulin --out json  # Run coverage\n   127→```\n   128→\n   129→## Project Structure\n   130→...\n   131→```\n   132→\n   133→### Previous Story Intelligence (9-4)\n   134→\n   135→- `generateDockerfileTemplate` signature change pattern: accept `string | null | StackDetection[]`, detect at runtime with `Array.isArray(second)`. Reuse same pattern for `generateAgentsMdContent`.\n   136→- `init-project.ts` has `allStacks` at L69 — already available; no new detection needed.\n   137→- `getStackLabel()` already handles arrays — confirmed in story 9-3 implementation.\n   138→- Test count: 3131 tests pass, 97.05% coverage after story 9-4.\n   139→\n   140→### Files to Change\n   141→\n   142→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Update `generateAgentsMdContent()` to accept `StackDetection[]`, update `ScaffoldDocsOptions` to include `stacks`, update `scaffoldDocs()` to pass stacks\n   143→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Pass `allStacks` to `scaffoldDocs()` via `stacks` option\n   144→- `src/modules/verify/env.ts` — Replace `detectStack()` with `detectStacks()` in `detectProjectType()`\n   145→- `src/commands/teardown.ts` — Replace `state.stack === 'nodejs'` with `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs')` fallback\n   146→- `src/templates/readme.ts` — Update `getInstallCommand()` to accept `string | string[] | null` for multi-stack install commands, update `ReadmeTemplateConfig.stack` type\n   147→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — Add multi-stack AGENTS.md tests, verify getProjectName multi-file discovery\n   148→- `src/templates/__tests__/readme.test.ts` — Add multi-stack install command tests (create if absent)\n   149→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/env.test.ts` — Add detectProjectType multi-stack test\n   150→\n   151→### References\n   152→\n   153→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-stack-support.md — Story 9-5]\n   154→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/tech-spec-multi-stack-support.md — Task 6, FR8]\n   155→- [Source: src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts — current implementation, 229 lines]\n   156→- [Source: src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts — existing tests, 256 lines]\n   157→- [Source: src/modules/verify/env.ts — detectProjectType at L69-79]\n   158→- [Source: src/commands/teardown.ts — state.stack reference at L190]\n   159→- [Source: src/templates/readme.ts — getInstallCommand at L72-77]\n   160→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation.md — previous story learnings]\n   161→\n   162→## Dev Agent Record\n   163→\n   164→### Implementation Plan\n   165→\n   166→- Task 1: Updated `generateAgentsMdContent()` signature to `(projectDir, stack: string | StackDetection[] | null)`. Added `generateMultiStackAgentsMd()` helper for array path. Root stacks (dir='.') get bare commands; subdir stacks get `cd {dir} &&` prefix.\n   167→- Task 2: Added `stacks?: StackDetection[]` to `ScaffoldDocsOptions`. `scaffoldDocs()` passes stacks to both AGENTS.md and README generation when multiple stacks detected.\n   168→- Task 3: Changed `ReadmeTemplateConfig.stack` to `string | string[] | null`. Exported `getInstallCommand()` with array support. Uses `getSingleInstallCommand()` helper with deduplication for arrays.\n   169→- Task 4: Replaced `detectStack()` with `detectStacks()` in `verify/env.ts`. Derives primary from root detection. Return type unchanged.\n   170→- Task 5: Updated teardown condition to `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs') ?? state.stack === 'nodejs'` for backward compat.\n   171→- Tasks 6-8: Added 18 new tests across docs-scaffold, readme, verify-env, and teardown test files.\n   172→- Task 9: Full suite passes — 3149 tests, 0 regressions.\n   173→\n   174→### Completion Notes\n   175→\n   176→All 9 tasks and all subtasks completed. 18 new tests added (5 multi-stack AGENTS.md, 8 readme template, 1 detectProjectType multi-stack, 1 teardown multi-stack, 3 existing tests updated for detectStacks). Full backward compatibility preserved — all existing single-stack callers continue to work unchanged.\n   177→\n   178→## File List\n   179→\n   180→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — modified (added StackDetection import, multi-stack AGENTS.md generation, ScaffoldDocsOptions.stacks, multi-stack README passthrough)\n   181→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — modified (pass allStacks to scaffoldDocs)\n   182→- `src/modules/verify/env.ts` — modified (replaced detectStack with detectStacks in detectProjectType)\n   183→- `src/commands/teardown.ts` — modified (state.stacks?.includes('nodejs') fallback)\n   184→- `src/templates/readme.ts` — modified (ReadmeTemplateConfig.stack type, getInstallCommand multi-stack, exported getInstallCommand)\n   185→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — modified (added 5 multi-stack AGENTS.md tests)\n   186→- `src/templates/__tests__/readme.test.ts` — created (8 tests for getInstallCommand and readmeTemplate multi-stack)\n   187→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-env.test.ts` — modified (updated mocks for detectStacks, added multi-stack detectProjectType test, updated existing tests)\n   188→- `src/commands/__tests__/teardown.test.ts` — modified (added multi-stack OTLP cleanup test)\n   189→\n   190→## Change Log\n   191→\n   192→- Story 9.5 implemented: Multi-stack docs and remaining consumers (Date: 2026-03-23)\n   193→\n   194→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   195→## Verification Requirements\n   196→\n   197→- [x] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers.proof.md`)\n   198→- [x] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   199→- [x] Test coverage meets target (90%+)\n   200→\n   201→## Documentation Requirements\n   202→\n   203→- [x] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   204→- [x] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers.md`\n   205→\n   206→## Testing Requirements\n   207→\n   208→- [x] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   209→- [x] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   210→- [x] Coverage target: 90%+\n   211→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   212→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017stQocDjYtQWzyiuCXnw1e","session_id":"58ae4f51-bff6-4a66-807a-d4f10c8bdaa3","uuid":"ecaf3234-49da-4166-8d5e-e976e664c5cc","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:51:09.199Z"}
