{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017stQocDjYtQWzyiuCXnw1e","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## CODE REVIEW FINDINGS\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers.md`\n**Git vs Story Discrepancies:** 0 (all files in story File List have corresponding git changes)\n**Issues Found:** 2 High, 2 Medium, 2 Low\n\n### HIGH Issues (Fixed)\n\n1. **Single-element `StackDetection[]` bypasses single-stack path** (`src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts:68-72`). `generateAgentsMdContent` used `Array.isArray(stack)` without checking length, so `[{stack:'nodejs', dir:'.'}]` produced multi-stack output with `###` subsections instead of the expected flat single-stack format. The `scaffoldDocs` caller guarded with `length > 1`, masking the bug from end-to-end, but the public API was broken for direct callers. **Fixed:** Added `length > 1` guard and single-element unwrap.\n\n2. **Empty `StackDetection[]` produced degenerate output** (`src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts:68-72`). An empty array `[]` entered the multi-stack path and produced an AGENTS.md with blank Language/Runtime and no build commands. **Fixed:** Empty arrays now fall through to the `null` (unknown stack) path.\n\n### MEDIUM Issues (Fixed)\n\n3. **`getInstallCommand('rust')` returned `cargo build` instead of an install command** (`src/templates/readme.ts:84`). The README template's \"Install\" section showed `cargo build` for rust, which is a build command, not an install command. Inconsistent with the function's contract and other stacks which return actual install commands. **Fixed:** Changed to `cargo install codeharness`.\n\n4. **No test coverage for `scaffoldDocs` multi-stack passthrough** (AC5). All `scaffoldDocs` tests used `{ stack: 'nodejs', isJson: false }` — none tested the `stacks` option. **Fixed:** Added 2 integration tests: one verifying multi-stack `stacks` generates subsectioned AGENTS.md, another verifying single-element `stacks` falls back to flat output.\n\n### Fixes Applied\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Array length guard, empty-array handling, extracted `stackDisplayName()` helper\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/templates/readme.ts` — `cargo build` -> `cargo install codeharness`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — 4 new tests (single-element array, empty array, scaffoldDocs multi-stack, scaffoldDocs single-stack)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/templates/__tests__/readme.test.ts` — Updated assertions and test name for rust install command\n\n### Post-fix Results\n\n- **Tests:** 3153 passed (115 suites), 0 failures\n- **BATS:** 307 passed, 0 failures\n- **Coverage:** 97.05% overall, all 123 files above 80% per-file floor\n- **Story status:** Updated to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- HIGH: Single-element `StackDetection[]` took multi-stack path, producing wrong output format for direct callers of `generateAgentsMdContent`. Fixed.\n- HIGH: Empty `StackDetection[]` produced degenerate AGENTS.md with no stack info. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `getInstallCommand('rust')` returned `cargo build` (build command) instead of an install command. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Zero test coverage for `scaffoldDocs` with `stacks` option (AC5 integration gap). Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt):**\n- LOW: Duplicated stack-to-label mapping still exists between `getStackLabel()` (includes file-type suffixes like `(package.json)`) and the new `stackDisplayName()` (bare names like `Node.js`). Two separate helpers exist for slightly different formatting. Could be unified with a parameter.\n- LOW: `verify-env.test.ts` still imports and mocks `detectStack` (singular) at lines 35, 41, 56 even though `env.ts` no longer uses it. The `mockDetectStack` variable i