eneration — verify (2026-03-23T15:33Z)\n    94→\n    95→- **Time constraint:** Verification started but session time budget exhausted before verifier could complete\n    96→- **State:** Docker container running, verifier session spawned but still in progress\n    97→- **Story left at:** `verifying` — next session will pick it up as Tier C (verifying without proof)\n    98→\n    99→---\n   100→\n   101→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 10)\n   102→\n   103→### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — create-story (2026-03-23T15:41Z)\n   104→\n   105→- **Ambiguity in epic AC4:** Original epic says verify/env.ts uses `stacks.includes('nodejs')` but actual code calls `detectStack()` directly, not state-based. AC rewritten to reflect actual code path.\n   106→- **ACs already satisfied:** AC2 (getStackLabel arrays) and AC3 (getProjectName multi-file) already implemented from story 9-3. Kept as verify-not-reimplement ACs.\n   107→- **File size risk:** `docs-scaffold.ts` at 229/300 lines, adding multi-stack AGENTS.md generation brings it close to ceiling.\n   108→- **No `readme.test.ts` found:** May need new test file for readme template changes.\n   109→\n   110→### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — dev-story (2026-03-23T15:46Z)\n   111→\n   112→- **File size risk:** `docs-scaffold.ts` grew from 229 to ~295 lines — under 300 limit but very close. Future extraction needed.\n   113→- **AC text mismatch:** Story AC mentions `npm ci` but template uses `npm install`. Tests match actual template behavior.\n   114→- **Test ripple effect:** ~15 existing verify-env tests needed updating to add `mockDetectStacks` calls due to detection method change.\n   115→- **AC7 logic difference:** AC specifies `state.stacks?.[0]` but implementation uses `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs')` which is more correct (checks anywhere in array).\n   116→\n   117→### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — code-review (2026-03-23T15:51Z)\n   118→\n   119→- **HIGH (fixed):** Single-element `StackDetection[]` bypassed single-stack path — direct callers of `generateAgentsMdContent` got wrong format.\n   120→- **HIGH (fixed):** Empty `StackDetection[]` produced degenerate AGENTS.md with no stack info.\n   121→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `getInstallCommand('rust')` returned `cargo build` instead of install command.\n   122→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Zero test coverage for `scaffoldDocs` with `stacks` option (AC5 gap). Added 2 integration tests.\n   123→- **LOW (not fixed):** Duplicated stack-to-label mapping between `getStackLabel()` and `stackDisplayName()`.\n   124→- **LOW (not fixed):** `verify-env.test.ts` still imports/mocks stale `detectStack` (singular).\n   125→- **Coverage:** 97.05% overall, all files above 80% floor. 3153 tests pass.\n   126→\n   127→### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — verify (2026-03-23T16:04Z)\n   128→\n   129→- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — session time budget exhausted (27/30 min used, <3 min remaining)\n   130→- **Story left at:** `verifying` — next session will pick it up as Tier C (verifying without proof)\n   131→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01W234qdt5ugaZ1DWce4cZWg","session_id":"58ae4f51-bff6-4a66-807a-d4f10c8bdaa3","uuid":"686bbc67-33a6-4c05-ab23-2f2e5f5fb876","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:04:48.131Z"}
